      • returnFormWithSectionFields

        protected org.json.JSONArray returnFormWithSectionFields(org.json.JSONObject sectionJson,
                                                         boolean popup)
                                                  throws org.json.JSONException
        Get form fields from JSON forms that have sections in the form steps. The JSONObject JSONObject argument is the object after getting the section in the specified step name The popup Boolean argument is a boolean value to let the function know that the form is being executed on a popup and not the main android view.

        This function returns a JSONArray JSONArray of the fields contained in the section for the given step

        Parameters:
        sectionJson -
        popup -
        Returns:
        Throws:
        org.json.JSONException

        protected org.json.JSONArray returnWithFormFields(org.json.JSONObject parentJson,
                                                  boolean popup)
                                           throws org.json.JSONException
        Get the form fields for the JSON forms that do not use the sections in the steps The JSONObject JSONObject argument is the object after getting the step name The popup boolean argument is a boolean value to let the function know that the form is being executed on a popup and not the main android view.

        This function returns a JSONArray JSONArray of the fields contained in the step

        Parameters:
        parentJson -
        popup -
        Returns:
        fields
        Throws:
